[ANALYSIS]
The experiment `bow_advanced_opt_20260514_115919_run_02` successfully executed with an F1 score of 0.7235 and accuracy of 0.765, indicating that the advanced Bag of Words (BoW) model with optimized parameters performed well on the validation set. The use of character-level n-grams (min=3, max=5) and word-level n-grams (max=2) likely contributed to capturing more nuanced patterns in the text data. However, the relatively low F1 score suggests that there is still room for improvement in terms of precision and recall, possibly due to class imbalance or insufficient feature representation.

